title: The T-Bones - No Matter What Shape (320)
description:
The T-Bones - No Matter What Shape (Your Stomach's In) (320)

The T-Bones (the American group name, not the UK band of the same name) was an invented name for a group of session musicians brought together by Liberty Records to record generic surf and hot rod instrumentals; music made popular in the early sixties by groups like The Ventures and The Marketts.  The T-Bones became a victim of their own success when they recorded their own version of a catchy jingle used by Alka-Seltzer, calling it "No Matter What Shape (Your Stomach's In)".  The song became a hit in 1965 and Liberty was compelled to come up with a performing version of the group to follow up on the song's success.
